Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[For further details, including a table of the 10 reference strains
most related to "O/Ganghwa/KOR/2010", subscribers may refer to the
above URL. Similarly to the serotype O isolates from Hong Kong, the
reference strain found most related to the S.Korean strain is
"O/MYA/7/98 (DQ164925)".

According to the results of this test, the South Korean strain is
closely related to the Hong Kong strain, which may be regarded as
representing the serotype O virus circulating in China since early
2010 (or earlier?!).

In case the spread of the virus is continued, the South Korean
authorities may eventually have to consider the application of
vaccination. So far, they have refrained from doing so in order to
enable an early regaining of the FMD-free status. - Mod.AS]
